uk.ac.ox.cs.diadem.oxpath.utils

Interface OXPathCache

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Extractor, PAATEval_
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    NewSimpleExtractor, OXPathMemoizer, OXPathMemoizerNaive, SimpleExtractor

    public interface OXPathCache
    Interface that all OXPath memoized functions must support so that cached data relating to a page, P, can be cleared once P is closed by PAAT. In most implementations, this function will be only a filler, as the proxy's implementation will override this method and not the method specified in this object.
    Author:
    AndrewJSel

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Boolean clear(DOMDocument page)
      Clears all memoized data for the input DOMDocument.

    • Method Detail

      • clear

        Boolean clear(DOMDocument page)
        Clears all memoized data for the input DOMDocument. Will be overridden as long as a proxy object is used (should always be used for OXPath classes overridding this method).
        Parameters:
        page - DOMDocument we are removing all memoized results for, presumably because the page is being closed in PAAT
